# MonoOS вҖ” Full Operating System Implementation Plan

> **Goal**: Build a custom x86 operating system from scratch in C and x86 Assembly, featuring its own kernel, package manager, and desktop environment вҖ” capable of being daily-driven.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **This is a massive multi-phase project.** I'll implement it incrementally, starting with Phase 1 (bootable kernel). Each phase builds on the previous one and produces a testable artifact (ISO image).

> [!WARNING]
> **Cross-compiler required.** We need an `i686-elf-gcc` cross-compiler toolchain to build for bare-metal x86. I'll provide build instructions, but you'll need to either:
> - Install WSL2 with the toolchain, **or**
> - Use a Docker container with the toolchain pre-installed
> 
> You'll also need **QEMU** to test-run the OS in a virtual machine.

> [!CAUTION]
> **Daily-driving an OS built from scratch** requires years of work for full hardware support. My plan gets you to a working graphical OS with core functionality. True daily-driving (web browsing, media, etc.) is a long-term evolution beyond the initial build.

---

