## Proposed Changes вҖ” Phase 1: Bootable Kernel

We start here. This phase produces a bootable ISO that enters the Dori kernel shell.

### Project Structure

#### [NEW] [Makefile](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/Makefile)
- Master build system: cross-compile all [.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/main.c) and `.asm` files
- Link with custom `linker.ld`
- Generate `monoos.iso` via `grub-mkrescue`
- Targets: `all`, `clean`, `run` (launches QEMU)

#### [NEW] [linker.ld](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/linker.ld)
- Dori kernel linker script: places `.text` at `0x100000` (1 MiB), followed by `.rodata`, `.data`, `.bss`
- Exports `_kernel_start`, `_kernel_end` symbols for memory manager

---

### Boot Layer

#### [NEW] [boot/multiboot.asm](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/boot/multiboot.asm)
- Multiboot2 header (magic, flags, checksum)
- Sets up initial stack (16 KiB)
- Calls `kernel_main()` in C
- Halts CPU on return

#### [NEW] [boot/gdt.asm](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/boot/gdt.asm)
- Global Descriptor Table flush routine (`gdt_flush`)

#### [NEW] [boot/idt.asm](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/boot/idt.asm)
- IDT load routine + ISR/IRQ stubs (0вҖ“47)
- Common interrupt handler that pushes state and calls C handler

---

### Kernel Core

#### [NEW] [kernel/kernel.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/kernel/kernel.c)
- `kernel_main()` вҖ” Dori kernel entry point
- Initializes GDT вҶ’ IDT вҶ’ PIC вҶ’ PIT вҶ’ keyboard вҶ’ terminal
- Drops into Dori shell loop

#### [NEW] [kernel/gdt.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/kernel/gdt.c)
- GDT entries: null, kernel code, kernel data, user code, user data, TSS
- `gdt_init()` function

#### [NEW] [kernel/idt.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/kernel/idt.c)
- 256-entry IDT
- ISR handlers for exceptions (0вҖ“31)
- IRQ routing (32вҖ“47)

#### [NEW] [kernel/pic.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/kernel/pic.c)
- 8259 PIC initialization (remap IRQs to 32вҖ“47)
- `pic_send_eoi()`

#### [NEW] [kernel/pit.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/kernel/pit.c)
- Programmable Interval Timer at 1000 Hz
- Global tick counter for scheduling

---

### Memory Management

#### [NEW] [kernel/pmm.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/kernel/pmm.c)
- Physical memory manager using bitmap allocator
- Reads multiboot memory map
- `pmm_alloc_frame()` / `pmm_free_frame()`

#### [NEW] [kernel/vmm.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/kernel/vmm.c)
- Virtual memory manager вҖ” page directory / page table management
- Identity-map first 4 MiB, map kernel higher
- `vmm_map_page()` / `vmm_unmap_page()`

#### [NEW] [kernel/heap.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/kernel/heap.c)
- Kernel heap: linked-list first-fit allocator
- `kmalloc()`, `kfree()`, `kmalloc_aligned()`

---

### Drivers

#### [NEW] [drivers/vga.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/drivers/vga.c)
- VGA text-mode driver (80Г—25, color)
- `vga_putchar()`, `vga_puts()`, `vga_clear()`, `vga_set_color()`
- Scrolling support

#### [NEW] [drivers/keyboard.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/drivers/keyboard.c)
- PS/2 keyboard driver (IRQ1)
- Scancode set 1 вҶ’ ASCII translation
- Circular input buffer

#### [NEW] [drivers/serial.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/drivers/serial.c)
- COM1 serial output for debug logging

---

### Kernel Shell

#### [NEW] [kernel/kshell.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/kernel/kshell.c)
- **Dori Shell (dsh)** вҖ” command-line shell running in kernel mode
- Built-in commands: `help`, `clear`, `meminfo`, `reboot`, `halt`, `echo`, `ver`
- Command parser and dispatcher

---

### Headers

#### [NEW] [include/](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/include/)
- Header files for all modules:
  - `kernel.h`, `gdt.h`, `idt.h`, `isr.h`, `pic.h`, `pit.h`
  - `pmm.h`, `vmm.h`, `heap.h`
  - `vga.h`, `keyboard.h`, `serial.h`
  - `kshell.h`
  - `types.h` (uint8_t, uint32_t, size_t, etc.)
  - `string.h` (memset, memcpy, strlen, strcmp)
  - `io.h` (inb, outb, inw, outw port I/O)

#### [NEW] [lib/string.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/lib/string.c)
- Freestanding string/memory utilities: `memset`, `memcpy`, `memmove`, `strlen`, `strcmp`, `strncmp`, `strcpy`, `itoa`

---

### GRUB Config

#### [NEW] [iso/boot/grub/grub.cfg](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/iso/boot/grub/grub.cfg)
- GRUB menu entry: "MonoOS v0.1 вҖ” Dori Kernel"
- `multiboot2 /boot/dori.kernel`

---

### Cleanup

#### [DELETE] [kernel.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/kernel.c)
#### [DELETE] [main.c](file:///c:/Users/Asus/Desktop/MonoOs/main.c)
